<% layout("../layouts/boilerplate.ejs") %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/pages/accessibility-assignment.css">

<div class="info-page">
    <div class="info-container">
        <div class="page-header">
            <i class="bi bi-universal-access"></i>
            <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
            <p>
                VibeStay is committed to ensuring that our platform is accessible
                and usable for everyone, regardless of ability, technology, or circumstances.
            </p>
        </div>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-heart-fill"></i>
                Our Commitment
            </h2>
            <p>
                We strive to provide an inclusive experience for all users.
                Accessibility is an ongoing effort, and we continuously work
                to improve the usability of our platform for everyone.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-display-fill"></i>
                Accessible Website Design
            </h2>

            <ul>
                <li>Clear navigation and page structure.</li>
                <li>Readable typography and spacing.</li>
                <li>Responsive layouts across devices.</li>
                <li>Consistent interface elements.</li>
                <li>Accessible forms and controls.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-keyboard-fill"></i>
                Keyboard Navigation
            </h2>

            <p>
                We aim to ensure that essential platform features can be
                accessed using a keyboard, helping users who may not use
                a mouse or touch-based devices.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-eye-fill"></i>
                Visual Accessibility
            </h2>
            <p>
                We work to maintain sufficient color contrast, clear labels,
                and understandable content to improve readability and
                usability for users with visual impairments.
            </p>

            <div class="accessibility-note">
                <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill"></i>
                <span>
                    Users may also use browser accessibility tools, zoom features,
                    and assistive technologies while using VibeStay.
                </span>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-volume-up-fill"></i>
                Assistive Technologies
            </h2>
            <p>
                We aim to support commonly used assistive technologies,
                including screen readers, keyboard-only navigation,
                and browser accessibility features whenever possible.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-phone-fill"></i>
                Mobile Accessibility
            </h2>
            <p>
                VibeStay is designed to function across a wide range of devices,
                including smartphones, tablets, and desktop computers,
                ensuring accessibility on different screen sizes.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-arrow-repeat"></i>
                Continuous Improvement
            </h2>
            <p>
                Accessibility is an ongoing process. We regularly review and
                improve our platform to identify and address potential barriers
                that may affect users.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-chat-dots-fill"></i>
                Feedback & Support
            </h2>
            <p>
                If you encounter accessibility issues or have suggestions for
                improving the accessibility of VibeStay, please contact our
                support team. Your feedback helps us create a better experience
                for everyone.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>